deep and violent feelings his book would stir up among devout 
moslems dahl wrote 
this kind of sensationalism does indeed get an indifferent 
book on the top of the bestseller list but to my mind it is a 
cheap way of doing it 
dahl worked for a number of childrens charities and recently 
donated the manuscript and copyright of his story the vicar of 
nibbleswicke to the british dyslexia institute 
dahl was born sept 13 1916 in wales the son of norwegian 
parents 
during world war ii he was a royal air force fighter pilot and 
was seriously wounded over the libyan desert he recovered in time 
to fight against pronazi forces in syria 
he began his writing career when the novelist cs forester 
asked him for an account of his air force experiences and the story 
was published in the saturday evening post 
he is survived by one son and three daughters by his marriage to 
ms neal another daughter is deceased 
funeral arrangements were not immediately announced 
