initiation rite a young man seeking to marry or pass into manhood 
had to bring back a head usually of his enemy 
some of the skulls contain holes made with primitive tools 
shahrum explained that people in certain societies believed that 
headaches were caused by evil spirits so holes were made in the 
skulls to free the spirits the cure was no doubt more painful than 
the headache 
an example comes from africa in 1957 an expedition encountered 
a living example of the skullboring practice known as trephination 
a man from the tibu tribe he had two huge scars in his scalp and 
carried in his pocket two fragments of his own skull 
