<TEXT>
the public got its first full look at president 
mikhail s gorbachevs plans for sharing power with the 15 soviet 
republics today when major newspapers published a draft of his 
proposed union treaty 
the proposed treaty represented the central governments latest 
attempt to appease secession movements by the republics and smaller 
regions while creating a uniform marketoriented economic system 
at a news conference friday night gorbachev warned that a 
breakup of the soviet union could lead to bloodshed and civil 
conflict and said he would use all his constitutional powers to 
prevent it 
publication of the draft treaty gave the public its first 
glimpse of the proposal in full designed as a charter for a new 
union of sovereign soviet republics 
the draft has already been submitted to the supreme soviet 
legislature and the parliaments of the republics 
to date all but one of the republics kirgizia have declared 
some form of sovereignty 
the three baltic states estonia latvia and lithuania have 
declared independence and say they will not sign a new union 
treaty but they say they are willing to reach political and 
economic agreements with the soviet union and other republics 
the legislature of a fourth republic georgia on friday 
uninamously enacted a law declaring a period of transition in the 
republic pending the restoration of its complete national 
independence and sovereignty the newspaper pravda reported 
today 
during the transition pravda said the parliament of georgia 
regards the signing of a new union treaty as impossible 
at his news conference gorbachev made it clear that republics 
wanting to leave the union must hold a referendum as required 
under existing soviet law he said he would oppose any other form 
of dissolving the union 
if someone tried to impose such a policy it would result in 
bloodshed and civil conflict which would be unacceptable to the 
world community he said 
many of the treatys points were unveiled by gorbachev in the 
supreme soviet last weekend and legislators twice endorsed his 
proposals to reorganize the central government to carry out the 
treaty 
the draft provides for establishing the council of the 
federation which would consist of a vice president the first in 
soviet history and heads of the republics 
the council would determine the main directions of the unions 
domestic and foreign policies the tass news agency said 
the treaty also would create a presidential cabinet formed in 
agreement between the president and the surpeme soviet tass said 
the cabinet would replace the current council of ministers headed 
by prime minister nikolai i ryzhkov 
under the draft treaty each republic as a sovereign state 
has full state powers over its territory treaty participants 
regard the soviet union as a sovereign federative state formed as a 
result of the republics voluntary union 
republics would independently determine their state structure 
administrativeterritorial division and the system of the bodies of 
power and administration the draft says 
in defining the sharing of power between the kremlin and the 
republics the draft treaty proclaimed the supremacy of republic 
legislation over republics territories on all questions except 
those which are referred to the jurisdiction of the union 
the central government would be empowered to adopt a new 
constitution protect the countrys borders and ensure the states 
security the kremlin would continue to control the armed forces 
and be responsible for defense matters the space program railway 
air and sea travel and the administration of the fuel and energy 
system 
the kremlin would also determine the countrys economic 
development and the creation of conditions for the development of 
the allunion market 
