when sen dennis deconcini met with the 
nations top thrift regulator in 1987 he made references to a memo 
that proposed a deal favorable to sampl owner charles h keating jr 
according to a sworn statement before the senate ethics committee 
the question of whether the arizona democrat actually offered a 
deal on keatings behalf is crucial to the ethics investigation of 
deconcini and four senate colleagues 
deconcini has repeatedly denied making such an offer the sworn 
statement given by someone who did not attend the 1987 meeting 
says only that deconcini made verbal references to a memo 
outlining a proposal for keating 
the ethics committee is trying to determine whether the 
