<TEXT>
suddenly it all looks gray the prime minister 
who told britons not to be moaning minnies who bustled around 
the globe handbag at the ready who stamped her authority on this 
nation as no other leader since winston churchill is finished 
margaret thatcher went as she came eyes ablaze in the house of 
commons seeking no sympathy and admitting no error though she had 
been overthrown by her own conservative party 
some loyalists and some who had abandoned her were near tears 
but she didnt flinch as she headed into the house of commons to 
defend her record against an opposition noconfidence motion just 
hours after admitting defeat 
im enjoying this she shouted during one raucous 
interruption 
style was part of the substance of margaret thatcher who 
imposed her personality on britain for more than 11 years it was 
her great strength and ultimately her tragic flaw 
fifty percent of thatcherism was this extraordinary style 
this character this abrasion said biographer hugo young the 
power of a person to dominate events and the way we see them to 
dominate our conversations and to make politics part of the saloon 
bar and drawing room life of britain 
challenged for the leadership and forced into a runoff the party 
elders said shed lose mrs thatcher withdrew thursday 
when the new leader of the party and the government is chosen 
this week by conservative legislators it will be the end of the 
thatcher era 
in the end it came over europe in part it was her total 
resistance to a single european currency as opposed to the 
neartotal resistance of most of the british cabinet that did it 
but mainly it was style dismissing proposals for political 
unity at a european commuinity summit in rome last month as a 
ragbag then turning on her resentful longsuffering deputy 
sir geoffrey howe at a cabinet meeting 
that was the last straw for howe who resigned and then 
unburdened himself in a savage resignation speech he had 
despaired he said of working for a woman who pursued a running 
argument with the official line of her own government 
margaret thatcher simply couldnt play along with her european 
partners on their wideranging but still vague proposals and wait 
as she insisted they would for things to fall apart in 
negotiations thats not my style she snapped at a questioner 
ten years ago she talked about the rush of adrenalin that came 
in a really good fight i stand there and i know now come on 
maggie you are wholly on your own no one can help you and i 
love it 
her ways were often reated as being peculiarly feminine and 
a handbagging became the cliche for one of her rages 
most women defend themselves she said on her 10th 
