unions or attending a cocktail party 
you have to put her in the same category as bloody mary queen 
elizabeth i queen anne and queen victoria said lord hailsham 
who served in thatcher cabinets from 197987 before retiring as 
lord chancellor the nations top legal officer 
her handling of men is not dissimilar if you had been a 
courtier of elizabeth i you would never quite know whether you 
were going to get the treatment of an admired friend or a poke in 
the eye with an umbrella 
like her friend ronald reagan she was devoted to a few clear 
ideas but unlike him she was seldom caught unprepared on the 
details and intricacies of policy 
she espoused what she called victorian values and her 
lectures to the nation ranged from the evils of socialism to the 
virtues of tidyness 
perhaps because of her mused the financial times britain no 
longer needs a strong leader one must hope so it added for 
it is most unlikely to enjoy such leadership again within a 
generation here was a thatcher when comes such another 
 
editors note maureen johnson is based in london and has 
covered british politics for the associated press for the past 
eight years 
