lafontaine concedes he misjudged kohls ability to retain voter 
loyalty despite the rapidly rising cost of unity 
violence has entered the campaign lafontaine and interior 
minister wolfgang schaeuble were targets of assassination attempts 
forty parties are running candidates but only a few have a real 
chance of winning seats in the bundestag as germany calls its 
parliament 
among the fringe groups are the farmers party of former east 
germany the grey ones a party for senior citizens the womens 
party and the xenophobic german national democrats 
the greens made up of leftists feminists and ecologists are 
worried about losing their traditional audiences to mainstream 
parties polls indicate some greens support is straying but not 
enough to shut them out of the bundestag 
on the far right the republican party had a meteoric rise for 
two years but has lost ground to mainstream parties analysts do 
not expect it to win the 5 percent of the vote needed to obtain 
parliament seats 
east germanys renamed communists are expected to get in even 
though they were caught sending party funds out of the country to 
avoid seizure the party is supported by many eastern germans but 
has a negligible following in former west germany 
the social democrats claim kohl is illequipped to clean up the 
badly polluted environment in eastern germany and is driving 
germany deeper into debt lafontaine has said for months that taxes 
will have to go up 
kohl says unity will not require a tax increase but that 
improving and protecting the environment may germanys most 
serious ecological problems are in the eastern regions 
