<TEXT>
here are highlights of the union treaty published 
saturday in pravda and other major soviet newspapers the following 
was translated from the russian by the associated press 
 
principles each republic is a sovereign state possessing full 
state power on its territory 
the ussr is a sovereign federative state based on the 
voluntary union of republics and administering state power within 
limits delegated by republics 
republics have the right of selfdetermination and 
selfgovernment resolution of all problems of the republics 
development 
republics determine their own state systems territorial 
division structure of organs of power 
 
structure of the union membership is voluntary and members of 
the union can question membership of one of the republics if it 
violates the treaty 
a citizen of a republic is a ussr citizen 
 
powers of the union the union can 
adopt and change constitution 
protect sovereignty and territorial integrity of the union 
defend state border protect state security defense 
set union foreign policy negotiate international treaties 
involving the union regulate the foreign economic activities of 
the soviet union and coordinate foreign economic activities of the 
republics control customs 
determine jointly with republics strategies of economic 
development create conditions for a union market a single fiscal 
and monetary policy based on single currency form and manage the 
union budget keep and on agreement of republics use gold and 
diamonds 
administer jointly with republics power fuel transport 
defense industries space research communications ecological 
policy establish guidelines for using natural resourses 
 
republics powers republics own land and natural resources on 
their territory and state property excluding that needed for 
exercising the powers of the union 
republics form their own budget determine taxes 
union taxes are for the union 
republics laws supreme unless they cover issues of unions 
authority 
union laws are supreme on issues of its authority 
disputes are resolved in commissions or the constitutional 
court 
</TEXT>
