<TEXT>
the commander of the soviet army in germany said 
84 soldiers had deserted in recent months but he denied news 
reports that black market dealing and mysterious deaths were 
rampant among the troops 
it was the first time the soviets have provided figures on the 
number of deserters 
gen boris vasilievich snetkov said 36 soldiers had left the 
army and turned themselves in to german authorities the other 48 
were missing he said 
the 380000 troops stationed in eastern germany are the largest 
contingent of the red army outside the soviet union they are to be 
withdrawn by 1994 
snetkov told a news conference that they face a relatively 
tense situation in the planned pullout from germany over the next 
four years 
but he denied reports that the contingent was falling apart 
plagued by low morale internal fighting and mysterious deaths 
recently german and soviet officials have expressed concern 
about the soviet troops still stationed in germany soviet 
president mikhail s gorbachev spoke of an antisoviet flavor 
during his meeting with chancellor helmut kohl in bonn earlier this 
month 
the troops have become a bitter remnant of the cold war 
occupation and many germans are anxious to see them leave the 
soldiers however face an uncertain future at home no guarantee 
of housing and the loss of access to western affluence and material 
goods 
germany has promised 8 billion to the soviet union to help 
finance the withdrawal 
in an interview published saturday in the eastern german daily 
junge welt a soviet lawyer and human rights activist was quoted as 
saying there were 800 deaths among soviet troops in 1988 and that 
he was investigating more than 2000 deaths in mysterious 
circumstances 
oleg liamin also was quoted as saying soviet barracks operate 
under a regime of terror where extortion and beatings among the 
troops are common 
other reports in the german press have said that red army 
soldiers desperate for german marks allegedly raid depots and 
trade weapons and uniforms on the black market 
soviet privates are paid only 16 a month 
snetkov called the reports of black market trade a lie and 
said the reported number of alleged deaths among the troops in 
eastern germany was ten times too high the actual number is 
about 100 a year he said 
we know our stay in this country brings inconveniences to the 
people he said but the people must understand that the forces 
must fulfill their training duties as army of the soviet union 
he said antisoviet sentiment by some germans was only making 
the pullout more difficult 
he said many soviet soldiers have been robbed by germans 
closer contact between the red army and the bundeswehr 
germanys armed force will ease tensions in the coming period he 
said 
