it was a rather minor disconnect last night because of some 
command errors transmitted from the ground the spacecraft didnt 
recognize a series of commands and decided to put itself in a safe 
position macmillan said it did not break communications the 
way it did in august it just reduced its information rate it sent 
back slow signals but no mapping data 
the spacecraft which circles venus every three hours and 15 
minutes lost about three orbits after it stopped mapping 
about 8 pm friday he said 
